The Nigerian Ambassador and Permanent Representative to the United Nations (UN), Prof. Tijjani Bande has been appointed as chairman of the African Group at the UN. This was made known by the spokesperson of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, George Ehidiamen Edokpa, in Abuja yesterday. Prof Bande replaced his Beninese counterpart, Jean Claude do Rego, during a ceremony at the African Union Observer mission in New York City, United States. During his acceptance speech, he pledged to focus on key issues facing the African continent including peace and security and the status of women. He also reassured the commitment of Nigeria to “strengthen the position” of the continent in the United Nations.  UN elects Nigeria’s Emuze into Rights panel Prof. Bathily confident in his chances to succeed Mrs. Zuma as AUC chair Why AU’s mass withdrawal should worry ICC – Prof Gambari